Authentication and Security
The TaxApp API employs strong security measures, including:

Password Hashing: User passwords are securely hashed and salted using bcrypt to ensure the confidentiality of user data.

Token-Based Authorization: To access protected endpoints, include the Authentication: token xyz header in your Postman requests, replacing xyz with the actual authentication token obtained during login.

Note
The reason for not providing a Docker image is due to an issue related to a C++ code dependency in the bcrypt package. Creating a Docker image with this issue is problematic. If you encounter any issues while setting up the application locally, please feel free to contact me for assistance.


